@Node "WI_PREFSEDIT" "PINT.guide/WI_PREFSEDIT"
@Next "RX_REXX"
@Prev "WI_LOGIN"
@Toc "Main"

The Preference Editor
=====================

   The Preference Editor is used for easy configuration of PINT.

   The Preference Editor has the following control items:

 @{" List           " Link "WI_PREFSEDIT_LISTVIEW"}		List of all variables.
 @{" Buttons        " Link "WI_PREFSEDIT_BUTTONS"}		Buttons in the Preference Editor.
 @{" Cycle Gadget   " Link "WI_PREFSEDIT_CYCLE"}		The cycle gadget.
 @{" Checkmarks     " Link "WI_PREFSEDIT_CMARK"}		The checkmarks.

   This editor will have more features in the future.

@Endnode

@Node "WI_PREFSEDIT_CMARK" "PINT.guide/WI_PREFSEDIT_CMARK"
@Next ""
@Prev ""
@Toc "Main"

Checkmarks
----------

   Toggle these checkmarks to display the variables that they represent.

@Endnode

@Node "WI_PREFSEDIT_LISTVIEW" "PINT.guide/WI_PREFSEDIT_LISTVIEW"
@Next ""
@Prev ""
@Toc "Main"

List of variables
-----------------

   This list has three columns;

      @{b}Scope@{ub}
         The scope that this variable will affect. Local or Global.
 
      @{b}Name@{ub}
         Name of the variable.

      @{b}Extension@{ub}
         Pattern of groups to cover. Leave this blank if you want it
         to work for all groups.
      
@EndNode

@Node "WI_PREFSEDIT_BUTTONS" "PINT.guide/WI_PREFSEDIT_BUTTONS"
@Next ""
@Prev ""
@Toc "Main"

Buttons
-------

@{b}New@{ub}
     Create a new variable for PINT.
     This will open the Preference Edit window.

     @{i}Keyboard shortcut:@{ui} 'N'

@{b}Delete@{ub}
     Remove the current variabel.

     @{i}Keyboard shortcut:@{ui} 'D'

@{b}Clone@{ub}
     Clone the current variabel.

     @{i}Keyboard shortcut:@{ui} 'D'

@{b}Rename@{ub}
     Rename the current variabel.

     @{i}Keyboard shortcut:@{ui} 'E'

@EndNode

@Node "WI_PREFSEDIT_CYCLE" "PINT.guide/WI_PREFSEDIT_CYCLE"
@Next ""
@Prev ""
@Toc "Main"

Cycle gadget
------------

@{b}Toggle@{ub}
     Toggle local/global for the current variable.

     @{i}Keyboard shortcut:@{ui} 'T'

@EndNode

@Node "WI_PREFSEDITVAR" "PINT.guide/WI_PREFSEDITVAR"
@Next ""
@Prev ""
@Toc "Main"

The Variable Edit window
==========================

   The Variable Edit window is used for easy configuration of 
a variable for PINT.

   @{b}Note!@{ub}
      All variables should currently be written as quoted.

      @{b}Example:@{ub}
      
           Single line:
             "Home of PINT"

           Multiple lines:
             "--\n\n"
             " /Magnus Heino\n"

   The Variable Edit window  has the following control items:

 @{" Text gadget   " Link "WI_PREFSEDITVAR_TEXT"}		The text gadget.
 @{" Buttons       " Link "WI_PREFSEDITVAR_BUTTONS"}		Buttons in the Variable Editor.
 @{" Cycle gadget  " Link "WI_PREFSEDITVAR_CYCLE"}		The cycle gadget.
 @{" String gadget " Link "WI_PREFSEDITVAR_STRING"}		The string gadget.

   This window also contains a group called "Contents". This is where the
value of the current variable is stored, and edited. The objects here will
change depending on the type of variable that you are editing. This will 
improve in the future, e.g. even more intuitive.

@Endnode

@Node "WI_PREFSEDITVAR_TEXT" "PINT.guide/WI_PREFSEDITVAR_TEXT"
@Next ""
@Prev ""
@Toc "Main"

Text gadget
-----------

   This gadgets contains the name of the variable.

   If you are editing a new variable, choose the name with the popup
listview to the left.

@EndNode

@Node "WI_PREFSEDITVAR_BUTTONS" "PINT.guide/WI_PREFSEDITVAR_BUTTONS"
@Next ""
@Prev ""
@Toc "Main"

Buttons
-------

@{b}Ok@{ub}
     Close window and apply all changes made.

     @{i}Keyboard shortcut:@{ui} 'O'

@{b}Cancel@{ub}
     Close window and discard all changes made.

     @{i}Keyboard shortcut:@{ui} 'C'

@EndNode

@Node "WI_PREFSEDITVAR_CYCLE" "PINT.guide/WI_PREFSEDITVAR_CYCLE"
@Next ""
@Prev ""
@Toc "Main"

Cycle gadget
------------

@{b}Scope@{ub}
     Set local/global for a new variable.

@EndNode

@Node "WI_PREFSEDITVAR_STRING" "PINT.guide/WI_PREFSEDITVAR_STRING"
@Next ""
@Prev ""
@Toc "Main"

String gadget
-------------

@{b}Extension@{ub}
     Use this gadget to set the pattern that this variable should affect.
     Leave it empty if you want it for all areas. There is a popup listview
     available to the left, containing all groups in the cache.

@EndNode

@Node "RX_REXX" "PINT.guide/RX_REXX"
@Next "RX_REXX"
@Prev "RX_REXX"
@Toc "Main"

ARexx Interface
***************

The ARexx commands
==================

   PINT has a powerful ARexx interface to control it partly from
external programs and to expand its functionality. Different commands
can be executed when opening or closing different windows and by
pressing function keys.

   For a description how to expand PINT via ARexx see
@{"PINT.Rexx" Link "CF_UMS_REXX"}.

   For a better unterstanding of the ARexx interface see the supplied
ARexx scripts.

   The @{i}Status@{ui} in the description of the ARexx commands is the status in
which PINT must be for executing the command.

   PINT knows the following ARexx commands:


Miscellaneous:

 @{" EXEC            " Link "RX_EXEC"}		Start a dos command
 @{" GETACCOUNT      " Link "RX_GETACC"}		Get the current account
 @{" GETSTRING       " Link "RX_GETSTRING"}		Open a string requester
 @{" INFO            " Link "RX_INFO"}		Ask for informations
 @{" QUIT            " Link "RX_QUIT"}		Quit PINT
 @{" REQUEST         " Link "RX_REQUEST"}		Open a requester
 @{" STATUS          " Link "RX_STATUS"}		Ask for current status

Group Window:

 @{" LOGIN           " Link "RX_LOGIN"}		Log into another account
 @{" RESCAN          " Link "RX_RESCAN"}		Rescan group list
 @{" SCANMODE        " Link "RX_SCANMODE"}		Change scanmodes

Article and Message Window:

 @{" ADDMSG          " Link "RX_ADDMSG"}		Add a message to the Article List
 @{" GETMSGNUM       " Link "RX_GETMSGNUM"}		Get the current messagenumber
 @{" GETSELMSGNUMS   " Link "RX_GETSELMSG"}		Get numbers of selected messages
 @{" GETTEMPFILENAME " Link "RX_GETTMPFNAME"}		Get filename of the attached file
 @{" REDISPLAY       " Link "RX_REDISPLAY"}		Redisplays the current message
 @{" RESCAN          " Link "RX_RESCAN"}		Rescan article list
 @{" SCANMODE        " Link "RX_SCANMODE"}		Change scanmodes
 @{" REMOVEDELETED   " Link "RX_REMDEL"}		Remove deleted messages from list
 @{" REPLACEMSGBODY  " Link "RX_REPLBODY"}		Replace the message body
 @{" SAVEMSGBODY     " Link "RX_SAVEMSGBODY"}		Save the message body

Scan Messages:

 @{" BEGINSCAN       " Link "RX_BEGINSCAN"}		Begin scan of messages
 @{" SCANMSG         " Link "RX_SCANMSG"}		Add a message to scan list
 @{" ENDSCAN         " Link "RX_ENDSCAN"}		End scan of messages
 @{" ABORTSCAN       " Link "RX_ABORTSCAN"}		Abort scan of messages

Adresss Book:
 @{" ADD             " Link "RX_ADD"}		Add entry to the address book
 @{" OPENGROUP       " Link "RX_OPENGROUP"}		Open a user group
 @{" ADDTOGROUP      " Link "RX_ADDTOGROUP"}		Add a person to the user group
 @{" CLOSEGROUP      " Link "RX_CLOSEGROUP"}		Close the user group


@EndNode

@Node "RX_EXEC" "PINT.guide/RX_EXEC"
@Next "RX_GETACC"
@Prev "RX_CLOSEGROUP"
@Toc "RX_REXX"

EXEC COMMAND/A/F
================

   With this command you can run programs from within PINT. This
is a workaround for the problem that the ARexx-server often has not a
usable path.

@{b}COMMAND/A/F@{ub}
     Command to be executed.

@{b}Status:@{ub} Any

@{b}Example:@{ub}

     To start ConfUMS use:
       EXEC "Confums"


@EndNode

@Node "RX_GETACC" "PINT.guide/RX_GETACC"
@Next "RX_GETSTRING"
@Prev "RX_EXEC"
@Toc "RX_REXX"

GETACCOUNT
==========

   Returns the UMS account which PINT currently uses. This account
can be copied with UMSDupAccount() and then it can be used for further
actions. If no user is logged into PINT this command will return 0.

@{b}Status:@{ub} Any


@EndNode

@Node "RX_GETSTRING" "PINT.guide/RX_GETSTRING"
@Next "RX_INFO"
@Prev "RX_GETACC"
@Toc "RX_REXX"

GETSTRING DEFAULT,TITLE/A,LABEL/A,SECRET/S
==========================================

   This command opens a string requester.

@{b}DEFAULT@{ub}
     Default settings for the contents.

@{b}TITLE/A@{ub}
     Title of the window.

@{b}LABEL/A@{ub}
     Name of the string gadget. If the Name contains an underscore the
     following character is used as the keyboard shortcut.

@{b}SECRET/S@{ub}
     If this option is used the input won't be readable.

@{b}Status:@{ub} Any

@{b}Example:@{ub}

       GETSTRING TITLE "PGP Decrypt" LABEL "_Phrase" SECRET


@EndNode

@Node "RX_INFO" "PINT.guide/RX_INFO"
@Next "RX_QUIT"
@Prev "RX_GETSTRING"
@Toc "RX_REXX"

INFO
====

   Returns some information about PINT.

   ITEM/A can have following values:

@{b}SCREEN@{ub}
     Returns the screen on which PINT has opened its windows.
     Other than MUI PINT returns always a correct name and not
     something like <default>.

@{b}VERSION@{ub}
     Returns the version number of PINT.

@{b}Status:@{ub} Any


@EndNode

@Node "RX_QUIT" "PINT.guide/RX_QUIT"
@Next "RX_REQUEST"
@Prev "RX_INFO"
@Toc "RX_REXX"

QUIT
====

   Quits PINT.

@{b}Status:@{ub} Any


@EndNode

@Node "RX_REQUEST" "PINT.guide/RX_REQUEST"
@Next "RX_STATUS"
@Prev "RX_QUIT"
@Toc "RX_REXX"

REQUEST TITLE/A,BUTTONS/A,MESSAGE/A
===================================

   Opens a normal requester with buttons.

@{b}TITLE/A@{ub}
     Title of the requester window.

@{b}BUTTONS/A@{ub}
     Definition of the buttons (MUI-style).

@{b}MESSAGE/A@{ub}
     Text of the requester.

@{b}Status:@{ub} Any

@{b}Example:@{ub}

       REQUEST "IN Request" "_Yes|Yes, of _course" "Do you like PINT?"


@EndNode

@Node "RX_STATUS" "PINT.guide/RX_STATUS"
@Next "RX_LOGIN"
@Prev "RX_REQUEST"
@Toc "RX_REXX"

STATUS
======

   Returns the status of PINT' ARexx Interface. The following
results are possible:

   @{b}*@{ub} QUERYBOOK - Address book is under construction.

   @{b}*@{ub} MESSAGE - Message window is active.

   @{b}*@{ub} ARTICLE - Article window is active.

   @{b}*@{ub} GROUP - Group window is active.

   @{b}*@{ub} DEFAULT - Default status.

@{b}Status:@{ub} Any


@EndNode

@Node "RX_LOGIN" "PINT.guide/RX_LOGIN"
@Next "RX_SCANMODE"
@Prev "RX_STATUS"
@Toc "RX_REXX"

LOGIN NAME/A,PASSWORD,SERVER/K
==============================

   Tries to change the UMS account used by PINT.

@{b}NAME/A@{ub}
     The name of the UMS user.

@{b}PASSWORD@{ub}
     The optional password of that UMS user.

@{b}SERVER/K@{ub}
     The optional name of the UMS server.

@{b}Status:@{ub} GROUP


@EndNode

@Node "RX_SCANMODE" "PINT.guide/RX_SCANMODE"
@Next "RX_RESCAN"
@Prev "RX_LOGIN"
@Toc "RX_SCANMODE"

SCANMODE INCMODE/A,ALLMODE/A
============================

   This command changes the current scanmodes for either the grouplist or the
current articlelist. If called from the article-window, the group will be
rescanned using the specified scanmode. This is only a temporary scanmode and
won't be saved in any way.

   Whether called from the group or articlewindow, a rescan will be made
afterwards.

An empty INCMODE- or ALLMODE-argument will leave the old setting.

@{b}INCMODE/A@{ub}
     The first scanmode. The following values are valid:

 Forward
 Backward
 All
 Selected
 PostPoned
 Archived
 Junked
 Parked
 FromUser
 ToUser

@{b}ALLMODE/A@{ub}
     The second scanmode. The following values are valid:

 Forward
 Backward
 All
 New
 Last 250
 Last 100
 Last 50
 Last 25


@{b}Status:@{ub} GROUP or ARTICLE


@EndNode

@Node "RX_RESCAN" "PINT.guide/RX_RESCAN"
@Next "RX_ADDMSG"
@Prev "RX_SCANMODE"
@Toc "RX_REXX"

RESCAN ALL/S
============

   If called from group list, the group list will be rescanned.

   If called from article list, the current group will be rescanned.
This only works for "pure" groups, not search-results or separator-groups. 

@{b}ALL/S@{ub}
     Rescan all messages

@{b}Status:@{ub} GROUP or ARTICLE


@EndNode

@Node "RX_ADDMSG" "PINT.guide/RX_ADDMSG"
@Next "RX_GETMSGNUM"
@Prev "RX_RESCAN"
@Toc "RX_REXX"

ADDMSG MSGNUM/A/N
=================

   Adds a message to the article list.

@{b}MSGNUM/A/N@{ub}
     Number of the message

@{b}Status:@{ub} ARTICLE or MESSAGE


@EndNode

@Node "RX_GETMSGNUM" "PINT.guide/RX_GETMSGNUM"
@Next "RX_GETSELMSG"
@Prev "RX_ADDMSG"
@Toc "RX_REXX"

GETMSGNUM DISPLAY,WRITTEN/S,REPLIED/S
=====================================

   Returns the number of the message which is currently displayed, 
replied to or written in the message window. This command only works 
if the message window is active or was the last active window.

@{b}DISPLAY@{ub}
     The msgid of the message displayed in the message-window. This only 
     works when the message-window is open.

@{b}WRITTEN/S@{ub}
     The msgid of the newly-written message. This is only available in the 
     WRITTEN or REPLIED Rexx-event.

@{b}REPLIED/S@{ub}
     The msgid of the newly-replied message. This is only available in the 
     REPLIED Rexx-event.

@{b}Status:@{ub} MESSAGE ARTICLE


@EndNode

@Node "RX_GETSELMSG" "PINT.guide/RX_GETSELMSG"
@Next "RX_GETTMPFNAME"
@Prev "RX_GETMSGNUM"
@Toc "RX_REXX"

GETSELMSGNUMS
=============

   This command returns the numbers of all selected messages in the
article window. All numbers a separated with spaces, f.e. "1521 1522
1537".

@{b}Status:@{ub} ARTICLE


@EndNode

@Node "RX_GETTMPFNAME" "PINT.guide/RX_GETTMPFNAME"
@Next "RX_REDISPLAY"
@Prev "RX_GETSELMSG"
@Toc "RX_REXX"

GETTEMPFILENAME
===============

   Returns the name of the file that is attached to the current message.

@{b}Status:@{ub} MESSAGE


@EndNode

@Node "RX_REDISPLAY" "PINT.guide/RX_REDISPLAY"
@Next "RX_REMDEL"
@Prev "RX_GETTMPFNAME"
@Toc "RX_REXX"

REDISPLAY
=========

   Redisplays the current message.

@{b}Status:@{ub} MESSAGE


@EndNode

@Node "RX_REMDEL" "PINT.guide/RX_REMDEL"
@Next "RX_REPLBODY"
@Prev "RX_REDISPLAY"
@Toc "RX_REXX"

REMOVEDELETED
=============

   Removes all messages deleted in the meantime from the article list.

   @{b}Status:@{ub} ARTICLE or MESSAGE


@EndNode

@Node "RX_REPLBODY" "PINT.guide/RX_REPLBODY"
@Next "RX_SAVEMSGBODY"
@Prev "RX_REMDEL"
@Toc "RX_REXX"

REPLACEMSGBODY FROM=WITH/A
==========================

   Replaces the text of the message currently shown in the message
window with the contents of a file.

@{b}Status:@{ub} MESSAGE

@{b}Example:@{ub}

       REPLACEMSGBODY WITH "Work:UMS/Read.me"


@EndNode

@Node "RX_SAVEMSGBODY" "PINT.guide/RX_SAVEMSGBODY"
@Next "RX_BEGINSCAN"
@Prev "RX_REPLBODY"
@Toc "RX_REXX"

SAVEMSGBODY MSG/A/M/N,TO/A/K
============================

   Saves the given message. You can give more than one message numbers
at once.

@{b}MSG/A/M/N@{ub}
     List of the message numbers.

@{b}TO@{ub}
     Name of the file to which the messages will be saved.

@{b}Status:@{ub} ARTICLE or MESSAGE


@EndNode

@Node "RX_BEGINSCAN" "PINT.guide/RX_BEGINSCAN"
@Next "RX_SCANMSG"
@Prev "RX_SAVEMSGBODY"
@Toc "RX_REXX"

BEGINSCAN
=========

   It is possible to scan virtual groups with PINT. With this
ARexx command the scan of this group is started.

@{b}Status:@{ub} GROUP

@{b}See also:@{ub} @{"SCANMSG" Link "RX_SCANMSG"} @{"ENDSCAN" Link "RX_ENDSCAN"} @{"ABORTSCAN" Link "RX_ABORTSCAN"}


@EndNode

@Node "RX_SCANMSG" "PINT.guide/RX_SCANMSG"
@Next "RX_ENDSCAN"
@Prev "RX_BEGINSCAN"
@Toc "RX_REXX"

SCANMSG MSGNUM/A/N
==================

   Adds a message to the virtual group.

@{b}Status:@{ub} Only after @{"BEGINSCAN" Link "RX_BEGINSCAN"}

@{b}See also:@{ub} @{"BEGINSCAN" Link "RX_BEGINSCAN"} @{"ENDSCAN" Link "RX_ENDSCAN"} @{"ABORTSCAN" Link "RX_ABORTSCAN"}


@EndNode

@Node "RX_ENDSCAN" "PINT.guide/RX_ENDSCAN"
@Next "RX_ABORTSCAN"
@Prev "RX_SCANMSG"
@Toc "RX_REXX"

ENDSCAN
=======

   Ends the scan of the virtual group and all messages which were added
with @{"SCANMSG" Link "RX_SCANMSG"} are shown in the article window.

@{b}Status:@{ub} Only after @{"BEGINSCAN" Link "RX_BEGINSCAN"}

@{b}See also:@{ub} @{"BEGINSCAN" Link "RX_BEGINSCAN"} @{"SCANMSG" Link "RX_SCANMSG"} @{"ABORTSCAN" Link "RX_ABORTSCAN"}


@EndNode

@Node "RX_ABORTSCAN" "PINT.guide/RX_ABORTSCAN"
@Next "RX_ADD"
@Prev "RX_ENDSCAN"
@Toc "RX_REXX"

ABORTSCAN
=========

   Aborts the scan of a virtual group.

@{b}Status:@{ub} Only after @{"BEGINSCAN" Link "RX_BEGINSCAN"}

@{b}See also:@{ub} @{"BEGINSCAN" Link "RX_BEGINSCAN"} @{"SCANMSG" Link "RX_SCANMSG"} @{"ENDSCAN" Link "RX_ENDSCAN"}


@EndNode

@Node "RX_ADD" "PINT.guide/RX_ADD"
@Next "RX_OPENGROUP"
@Prev "RX_ABORTSCAN"
@Toc "RX_REXX"

ADD NAME/A,ADDRESS/A,COMMENT/A
==============================

   PINT supports external address book programs to create its own
address book. With this command a person is added to the address book
of PINT.

@{b}NAME/A@{ub}
     Name of the person to be added.

@{b}ADDRESS/A@{ub}
     E-mail address of the person to be added.

@{b}COMMENT/A@{ub}
     Comment for the entry.

@{b}Status:@{ub} QUERYBOOK

@{b}Example:@{ub}

       ADD "David Rydh" "dary@lindesign.se" "Author of PINT"
     
     
     @{b}See also:@{ub} @{"PINT.Book" Link "CF_UMS_BOOK"} @{"Address book" Link "WI_BOOK"}


@EndNode

@Node "RX_OPENGROUP" "PINT.guide/RX_OPENGROUP"
@Next "RX_ADDTOGROUP"
@Prev "RX_ADD"
@Toc "RX_REXX"

OPENGROUP COMMENT/A
===================

   Opens a user group in the address book. A user group won't be
accepted if it is not closed.

@{b}Status:@{ub} QUERYBOOK

@{b}COMMENT/A@{ub}
     Comment for the user group to be opened.

@{b}See also:@{ub} @{"CLOSEGROUP" Link "RX_CLOSEGROUP"} @{"ADDTOGROUP" Link "RX_ADDTOGROUP"}


@EndNode

@Node "RX_ADDTOGROUP" "PINT.guide/RX_ADDTOGROUP"
@Next "RX_CLOSEGROUP"
@Prev "RX_OPENGROUP"
@Toc "RX_REXX"

ADDTOGROUP NAME/A,ADDRESS/A
===========================

   Adds a person to the actually opened user group.

@{b}NAME/A@{ub}
     Name of the person to be added.

@{b}ADDRESS/A@{ub}
     E-mail address of the person to be added.

@{b}Status:@{ub} QUERYBOOK

@{b}See also:@{ub} @{"OPENGROUP" Link "RX_OPENGROUP"} @{"CLOSEGROUP" Link "RX_CLOSEGROUP"}


@EndNode

@Node "RX_CLOSEGROUP" "PINT.guide/RX_CLOSEGROUP"
@Next "RX_EXEC"
@Prev "RX_ADDTOGROUP"
@Toc "RX_REXX"

CLOSEGROUP
==========

   Closes the actual user group.

@{b}Status:@{ub} QUERYBOOK

@{b}See also:@{ub} @{"OPENGROUP" Link "RX_OPENGROUP"} @{"ADDTOGROUP" Link "RX_ADDTOGROUP"}


@EndNode

